ated":null,"euaPurchased":null,"euaBalance":null}},{"portName":"Amsterdam","displayOrder":6,"co2":126.957600000000000000,"eeoi":22.585579402791844000,"aer":17.733156870001770000,"soxMt":0.079200000000000000,"sox":0.014089569184523920,"noxMt":3.960000000000000400,"nox":0.704478459226196100,"euEtsDetails":{"allowancePurchases":null,"eua":0.000000000000000000,"euaCostUSD":null,"euaCostEUR":null,"euaPriceUSD":null,"euaPriceEUR":null,"euaVerified":null,"euaEstimated":null,"euaPurchased":null,"euaBalance":null}}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2022-05-24T16:11:23.2","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Difference:    As always with these, Marquis changes quite a bit from the initial 1:1 estimate but very nice to see us still coming out on top, meaning our terms/demurrage rate are covering the changes accordingly.  Vessel ultimately discharged Thames, Amsterdam and Immingham in addition to Rotterdam but after waiting 2 days at Amsterdam the 1st time, they decided to move onto Rotterdam without discharging cargo and wanted us to come back to Amsterdam at end for final discharge.  This ended up adding deviation/interim port and covers about 50 mt LSGO consumption assisting the results.  After discharging Thames, vessel had engine issue which required us to wait for an escort tug\u2026for 4 days despite all best efforts!  This is offhire for NMM showing in this calc.  Port cost at St. Rose over $100k now mainly due to towage fuel surcharges we see with escalating diesel prices all over.  Bunkers higher due to 21 additional port days of which 13 days were recouped under interim port or laytime at $19,500/day.  Interesting to note but usually IMOIIMAX struggle to maintain 13 kts but on this laden passage averaged 13.3 which was good with Marquis being under time crunch as per fixture note below."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-05-12T17:06:54.51","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Off-hire due to unplanned main engine incident"}],"offhireList":[{"id":191139,"dateStartUt